st Indies|West Indies cricket championship]] after the tournament is suspended due to the pandemic.<ref>[https://apnews.com/435405d82ed4d043a7998c2a32fc8e87 Barbados declared winners of West Indies championship] AP, 24 Mar 2020</ref>\n*March 29 \u2013 The [[United States Coast Guard]] issues a safety bulletin for [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Florida|Florida]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Carolina|South Caroina]], and Puerto Rico stating that foreign-flagged vessels carrying more than 50 people should prepare to treat any sick passengers and crew on board and try to medically evacuate the very sick to their countries home countries.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=AP|title=Coast Guard: Cruise ships must stay at sea with sick onboard|author1=FREIDA FRISARO|author2=ADRIANA GOMEZ LICON |date=1 April 2020|url=https://news.yahoo.com/coast-guard-cruise-ships-must-122752320.html}}</ref>\n*March 30 \u2013 [[Spiritual Baptist/Shouter Liberation Day]], Trinidad and Tobago\n\n===April===\n*April 1\n**U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] announces that he is stepping up pressure on Venezuelan President [[Nicol\u00e1s Maduro]] after indicating Maduro on drug and terrorism charges. Trump sends anti-drug Navy ships and [[Airborne early warning and control|AWACS]] planes to the region near [[United States\u2013Venezuela relations|Venezuela]] in the largest military build-up in the region since the [[United States invasion of Panama|1989 invasion of Panama]] to remove General [[Manuel Noriega]] from power.<ref>[[United States\u2013Venezuela relations|Trump: US to deploy anti-drug Navy ships near Venezuela]] AP, 1 April 2020</ref>\n**Three Cuban dissidents, including [[Jos\u00e9 Daniel Ferrer]], arrested on October 1, 2019, have been released to [[house arrest]].<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/america-latina/2020/04/03/el-regimen-de-cuba-dicto-la-prision-domiciliaria-para-jose-daniel-ferrer-lider-opositor-en-la-isla-j